      {
        "position": 1,
        "title": "Big comfy dog bed",
        "text": "Dog mom review after getting the Sytopia 36-inch bed for my pup So first off, my dog immediately claimed it. Like no hesitation, no sniffing around for three days just straight up flopped down like “yep, this is mine now.” That’s usually a good sign in my house.The bed feels pretty sturdy when you first set it up. It’s got that thick egg-crate foam inside, so it’s not just a flimsy cushion on the floor. My dog actually looks more supported in it, especially when she’s stretched out or curled up for a long nap. I’ve definitely noticed she’s not shifting around as much trying to get comfy.The“waterproof/indestructible” claim… I’ll say it like it is: it’s tough, but not magic. It holds up way better than cheap beds, but if you’ve got a determined chewer, nothing is truly untouchable. For normal lounging, scratching, and daily dog chaos though it’s doing its job.",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "April 20, 2026",
        "author": "Amanda Sawyer",
        "author_link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGHTEIYT7IXNJQKBIXT32NWEIIEQ",
        "author_image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/amazon-avatars-global/794abd51-9856-4793-9eed-9520dad8bbf5._CR0%2C0%2C500%2C500_SX460_.jpg",
        "product": {
          "size": "36.0\"L x 27.0\"W x 3.0\"Th",
          "color": "Dark Grey"
        }
      },
      {
        "position": 2,
        "title": "thin bed, tough fabric on top.",
        "text": "I got the larger version of this, and love it. It has the bolsters. It is tough and confortable. However, within 32 days the zip pull broke off.I was so excited about the toughness and comfort when I received it, I order this for my smaller dog. This bed is thinner. It turns out it is almost as long as the lower pad of the big bed. I expected it to be thicker as it looks in the picture, so was disappointed. The cover does fit on easier. Hopefully the pull won't break. However, my dog does not use it, possibly due to the lack of bolsters. It is tough enough, but a very minimal bed, and not worth the price.I know from experience the bottom is the weakest point of these beds. I have a small bed with bolsters of similar fabric on the bottom with a hole chewed in the bottom. Often they don't focus on the bottom with the tougher beds. The dogs I have now don't chew up beds.",
        "rating": 4,
        "date": "April 13, 2026",
        "author": "northern blue",
        "author_link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHTVW3Q6J67O2S2U2SD4FEIX4BRQ",
        "author_image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/amazon-avatars-global/default.png",
        "product": {
          "size": "36.0\"L x 27.0\"W x 3.0\"Th",
          "color": "Brown"
        }
      },
      {
        "position": 3,
        "title": "Comfortable And Supportive Orthopedic Dog Bed",
        "text": "This 36-inch orthopedic dog bed is a nice size and holds my 65-pound Beagle-Basset mix perfectly. It is great that the cover is washable if it should ever need washing. We put this bed on a hammock bed in our outdoor room and put a more plush thinner hammock blanket cover over the top. It seems to provide superior support for my dogs as the middle layer between the hammock bed and the plush blanket. The cover is comfortable enough that it really doesn't need a top layer, but since this is indoors, it is nice to have the added comfort. As for its durability, that is hard to say at this time, but fortunately, my dogs aren't bed diggers and don't tend to chew or destroy their beds for fun or out frustration or boredom. I see some other reviews of this dog bed in which the dog owners lock their dogs in a kennel and then are surprised when the bed gets chewed up. Locked up dogs will do that out of frustration or boredom, and the bed isn't to blame for that. I will update this review at a later time if there is new information to share regarding durability. In the meantime, my dogs love it, and so I can recommend it.",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "April 1, 2026",
        "author": "Loves Dogs",
        "author_link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEGM7VDBTYLJEOQUFSXMMWANSNTA",
        "author_image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/amazon-avatars-global/3c8f0946-ee3b-4e70-a0cb-8dd4e227ce91._CR0%2C0%2C500%2C500_SX460_.jpeg",
