      {
        "position": 5,
        "title": "Excellent Quality Fabric / Eggcrate Soft & Firm",
        "text": "The product description of 60 pounds is very accurate relating to the size of the dog for this bed. Pictured in the photos is my 63 pound Samoyed, and I agree larger dogs wouldn't fit well on the bed. I disagree with a product title indicating this is for extra large dogs or giant dogs, that simply is not true. Sixty pounds is considered a medium dog and this bed definitely is for that weight and not much more!My Samoyed really liked the medium firmness of the bed, the eggcrate carton was soft yet supportive. It does distribute the dog's weight. The quality of the material was very good, it is durable and won't easily snag. I like the option of removing the cover to wash it, however it is a challenge to get the eggcrate pad back in the cover. It's much easier when two people are doing it, and I'd prefer that rather than having a skimpy pad. I do think it is very well made and the quality of the fabric is excellent. I think it's worth the 49.99 price.",
